The purpose of the Partnership is to engage in the following business activities:

{{business_purpose}}

The Partnership may also engage in any other lawful business activity as the Partners may agree upon from time to time.

Each Partner shall make the following initial capital contributions to the Partnership:

- {{partner_one_name}}: ${{partner_one_contribution}}
- {{partner_two_name}}: ${{partner_two_contribution}}

Additional capital contributions may be made by mutual agreement of the Partners. No Partner shall be required to make additional contributions without their consent.

Each Partner shall have an equal right to participate in the management of the Partnership. Decisions relating to the ordinary course of business shall be made by majority agreement of the Partners. The following decisions shall require the unanimous consent of all Partners:

(a) Sale or transfer of Partnership assets outside the ordinary course of business;
(b) Incurring debt in excess of $10,000;
(c) Admitting new Partners;
(d) Amending this Agreement;
(e) Dissolution of the Partnership.

A Partner may withdraw from the Partnership by providing ninety (90) days' written notice to the other Partners. Upon withdrawal, the withdrawing Partner shall be entitled to receive the value of their interest as determined by an independent valuation. The Partnership shall dissolve upon the occurrence of any of the following:

(a) Unanimous agreement of the Partners;
(b) The withdrawal, bankruptcy, or death of a Partner, unless the remaining Partners elect to continue;
(c) Any event that makes it unlawful for the Partnership to continue.
